# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using pyenv. See https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/blob/master/COMMANDS.md#pyenv-version-file
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different platforms or dependencies:
#   Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   According to poetry markup, it is recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   PDM stores project-wide configurations in .pdm.toml
.pdm.toml
